    • Constructor Detail

      • FileInputter

        public FileInputter(FileInputStream fis)
        Creates a FileInputter that reads it's input from the FileInputStream provided. This object will not close the stream, but future implementations may close it when hasNext() returns false.
        Parameters:
        fis - The input stream to use.

    • Method Detail

      • next

        public void next()
        Description copied from class: Inputter
        Returns the next character within the inputter. This is the only method that should increment the position variable. Making position protected allows classes that need to maniuplate position available to it, but this method will automatically increment the position by one.
        Overrides:
        next in class Inputter

        Determines whether the stream has any available bytes.
        Specified by:

      • lookAhead

        public char lookAhead()
        Looks ahead in the inputter without consuming the current character. This method has undefined behaviour at the end of the parser.
        Specified by:
        lookAhead in class Inputter
        Returns:
        The next character in the stream, if there is one.
